            <section class="prose">
              <h2>How this XP leveling calculator works</h2>
              <p>
                This tool is designed for any RPG, MMO, ARPG, gacha, or mobile
                game where you grind experience points (XP) to level up. Instead
                of being tied to a specific title, it lets you plug in your own
                XP curve and grind rate.
              </p>

              <h3>1. Choose or define the XP curve</h3>
              <p>
                Games rarely use a flat XP requirement. Higher levels usually
                need more XP. The calculator supports three modes:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Linear:</strong> every level requires the same XP as
                  level 2.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>RPG-style (quadratic):</strong> XP grows faster with
                  level. We approximate the XP needed to go from level
                  <em>L</em> to <em>L+1</em> as:
                </li>
              </ul>
              <div class="formula-box text-sm">
                <p>XP<sub>L→L+1</sub> = baseXP × (L)<sup>k</sup></p>
                <ul class="mt-2">
                  <li><code>baseXP</code> = XP required from level 1 → 2</li>
                  <li><code>L</code> = current level</li>
                  <li><code>k</code> = curve intensity (1.0–3.0)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Custom table:</strong> you paste the exact XP per
                  level from your game’s wiki or in‑game UI. Line 1 is XP from
                  level 1 → 2, line 2 is 2 → 3, and so on.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>2. XP required from your current to target level</h3>
              <p>
                The calculator sums the XP needed for each level-up between your
                current and target level, then subtracts any XP you already have
                in your current level:
              </p>
              <div class="formula-box text-sm">
                <p>
                  Total XP needed = \(\displaystyle \sum_{L =
                  L_{current}}^{L_{target}-1} XP_{L→L+1}\) − XP<sub
                    >already in current level</sub
                  >
                </p>
              </div>

              <h3>3. Actions, hours, and days to reach your goal</h3>
              <p>
                Once we know how much XP you need, we convert that into grind
                time using your XP source and pace:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>XP per action:</strong> XP per kill, quest, dungeon,
                  match, etc.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Actions per hour:</strong> how many of those you can
                  realistically do per hour.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>XP bonus multiplier:</strong> rested XP, double XP
                  events, boosters, etc.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <div class="formula-box text-sm">
                <p>
                  Effective XP per action = XP<sub>per action</sub> ×
                  bonusMultiplier
                </p>
                <p>
                  Actions required = Total XP needed ÷ Effective XP per action
                </p>
                <p>Hours required = Actions required ÷ Actions per hour</p>
                <p>
                  Days required = Hours required ÷ Hours per day you can play
                </p>
              </div>

              <h3>Tips for using this with your favorite game</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Look up the official or community XP table and paste it into
                  the <strong>Custom</strong> mode.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Measure your real actions per hour by timing a 10–15 minute
                  grind session.
                </li>
                <li>Adjust the XP bonus when events or boosters are active.</li>
                <li>
                  Use the per-level table to identify “spike” levels that need
                  extra planning.
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>Limitations</h3>
              <p>
                This calculator assumes a consistent XP rate. Real gameplay
                often includes downtime (travel, wipes, queues), variable XP
                rewards, and changing strategies. Treat the results as a
                planning baseline, not a guarantee.
              </p>
            </section>
